This paper deals with language modeling and automatic speech recognition (ASR), which are both subfields of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes extensions to neural cache models, which involve training and optimizing neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also evaluates the proposed models on ASR tasks, which falls under cs.SD (Sound) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper makes use of information weighting, which is a technique used in information retrieval and recommendation systems, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category as well.
